MICROSOFT TO PRESENT `SUPPORTING WINDOWS 95' AT SYSTEMS SUPPORT EXPO

YARMOUTH, Maine - Feb. 21, 1995 - When Windows 95 rolls out, the support
world needs to be ready.

To help attendees at Systems Support Expo prepare to support their
users, Microsoft will present "Supporting Windows 95" during the two-day
trade show. Systems Support Expo, sponsored by Service News, will be
held at Boston's World Trade Center on May 17-18.
