#1766

AER ENERGY TO DEVELOP LONG RUN-TIME BATTERY
OPTION FOR HP OmniBook 600 NOTEBOOK COMPUTER

SMYRNA, Ga. - Feb. 21, 1995 - AER Energy Resources Inc. today announced
it has started to develop a long run-time battery for the HP OmniBook
600 notebook PC from Hewlett-Packard Company.

AER Energy(TM) plans to offer the battery as an optional third party
accessory for the OmniBook PC. Depending on the user's work pattern, the
AER Energy optional battery currently under development has the
potential to power an OmniBook PC for 10 to 15 hours without recharging.
