#1770

NMN ASSOCIATES OFFERS SPEECH TECHNOLOGY COURSE

Detroit, Mich. - Feb. 22, 1995 - Responding to increasing demands
for a clear overview of speech processing technology, NMN
Associates has developed a course targeting technical managers
and developers who need to learn about this important field.

Designed for non-specialists, the goal of the course is to provide
participants with a structured understanding of the different speech
processing technologies available. Rather than emphasizing a
particular technology or implementation, the course examines the
relationships between important classes of speech technologies and
how to determine the best match for a particular application.

Conducted at the Westin Hotel in Detroit on May 8th, the course is
timed to coincide with the International Conference on Acoustics,
Speech and Signal Processing on May 9-12.
info: tel. 800-578-0756   Outside USA: +1-505-838-0756
Email: nmn@ic.mankato.mn.us
