#1771

FLASH CARD PRICES TO FALL SHARPLY THIS YEAR

SAN JOSE, Calif.- Feb. 21, 1995 - Dataquest predicts a sharp decline in
the price of flash cards by year-end making mobile computing options
more affordable for consumers.

"Developments in technology, resulting in sharply higher capacities and
lower pricing, are moving forward at an accelerated pace," said Rod
Watkins, industry analyst at Dataquest. "Although a rigid or tape drive
is still the domain of the technically adept, PCMCIA flash cards will
regularly be purchased, installed, configured, and used by the average
consumer."
