#1787

CRYSTAL COMPUTER NOW SHIPPING WORLD'S
FIRST PLUG AND PLAY SOUND CARDS

SAN JOSE, Calif. - Feb. 24, 1995 - Crystal Computer Corporation
announced today their initial production shipments of the world's first
genuine Plug and Play sound cards.

Available at leading computer retail outlets and catalogs later this
month, the new Crystalizer Plug and Play cards provide users an
automatic configuration and installation in IBM PC/AT and 100%
compatible computer systems. Moreover, they help get users up and
running immediately even in computers that do not yet support the Plug
and Play standard.
